Notes: The 'row_id' uniquely identifies each prescription record, making 'hasIdentifier' the most appropriate property to represent this as a unique identifier in RDF.
The 'patient_id' links to the patient entity involved in the prescription, aligning with the 'hasPatient' relationship.
The ATC code uniquely identifies a drug concept, making 'hasCode' on the Drug entity the best fit.
Diagnosis codes are best represented through the 'hasCode' property on the Diagnosis entity.
Creation date best maps to the 'hasDateTime' property with datatype dateTime.
Number of times per day is a quantitative measure, mapped to 'hasValue' under Quantity.
The dosage describes the active ingredient, best represented via 'hasActiveIngredient' on the Drug entity.
